A Kenilworth woman accused of orchestrating her husbands murder was released on R30 000 bail on Monday morning.Petina Coetzee made a brief appearance in the Wynberg Magistrate&#x2019;s Court for her bail application hearing.Coetzee is accused of trying to secure a killer to murder her husband Austin Coetzee.The 44-year-old mother of three was arrested last Tuesday morning by police who had been tipped off that she was planning the murder.Police say she was nabbed in a sting operation in the parking lot of the Lansdowne train station after handing over an undisclosed amount of money to the &#x201C;hitman&#x201D;Her bail conditions includes reporting to the Elsies River police station everyday, and handing in her passport.Coetzee is expected back in court on December 2. [email&#160;protected]